# Content Authoring

## Blog (`src/content/blog/copywriter-posts.ts`, `editorial-posts.ts`, merged in `posts.ts`)

- `BlogPost`: `slug`, `title`, `excerpt`, `categories[]`, `date`, `author`, `coverImage`, `content[]`, `headings[]`.
- Body uses light markdown: `##` / `###`, `-` lists, `**bold**`, `![alt](url)`, `> Tip:` / `> Summary:` — see `.cursor/skills/blog-content-authoring/SKILL.md`.
- Slugs: kebab-case, unique, stable (URLs depend on them).
- `headings[].id` must match `##` / `###` in content for anchors and build validation.
- On-page TOC and scroll-spy use **`level: 2` only**; `level: 3` entries sync `###` anchor ids but do not appear in TOC.
- Build validates `headings[]` sync with every `##` / `###` in `content`, image hosts, and `/blog/slug` links.
- `categories` is a non-empty array of valid `BlogCategory` keys (multiple badges per post).

## FAQ / pricing

- Keep structured data in `src/content/faqs.ts` and `src/content/pricing.ts`.
- UI reads content modules — avoid duplicating the same copy in components.

## Dates and locale

- ISO dates in content (`YYYY-MM-DD`); display formatting via `src/lib/blog.ts` / `toLocaleDateString("en-US")` until i18n exists.

## After adding blog posts

- No `generateStaticParams` change needed if slug is in `posts` array.
- Sitemap picks up slugs via `getAllSlugs()`.
